title: Walkers raise money for homeless in fifth annual Seattle-area...
text:
A Seattle-area group gathered Sunday morning to walk 22 miles—raising money for the homeless.
The walkers started at the Edmonds Dick’s location, and trekked to five others over the course of the day: Lake City, Holman Road, Wallingford, Broadway, and Queen Anne.
The Dick’s Walk-A-Thon started as an urban hike, founded by Ballard High School graduates four years ago.
#Seattle -area group gathers to walk 22 miles—raising money for the homeless >> http://t.co/e8HG3JmRD8 pic.twitter.com/TVkfg9dhjf
— KIRO 7 (@KIRO7Seattle) October 5, 2015 >> Follow along with the walkers, on this live map
Co-founder Lars Phillips is pictured to the left.
"For those who complete the entire trek we promise a cheeseburger will be waiting for you at Queen Anne!" wrote organizers.
